WEBVTT

00:04.104 --> 00:05.939
So what's on the agenda for tonight?

00:05.971 --> 00:09.543
I thought we might just
have a quiet night in.

00:09.575 --> 00:11.844
Come on.

00:13.622 --> 00:14.880
This way, Madame.

00:16.838 --> 00:19.306
What did you do?

00:26.916 --> 00:28.818
Thank you.

00:28.851 --> 00:29.953
You're out of your mind!

00:33.689 --> 00:35.892
It's spectacular.

00:35.924 --> 00:38.227
Happy anniversary.

00:38.428 --> 00:40.262
Happy anniversary.

00:48.436 --> 00:51.406
Hey, his lips are moving.

00:51.439 --> 00:53.334
You think he's trying to say something?

00:53.375 --> 00:55.345
Most likely an involuntary response

00:55.378 --> 00:57.607
to something in the Reverie program.

00:57.912 --> 00:59.682
Well, how can you know for sure?

00:59.714 --> 01:01.986
We can't.

01:02.618 --> 01:04.753
They brought in another one
this morning.

01:07.149 --> 01:08.291
That makes seven.

01:08.356 --> 01:09.725
I can count.

01:09.758 --> 01:11.360
I know you can count.

01:11.393 --> 01:12.743
What if this becomes an epidemic?

01:12.782 --> 01:14.997
Seven users isn't an epidemic.

01:15.031 --> 01:16.732
It's a fraction of a fraction.

01:16.765 --> 01:19.368
They're in a coma, Lexi...

01:19.467 --> 01:21.166
because of your program.

01:21.236 --> 01:23.319
My program is doing
exactly what it's supposed to.

01:23.361 --> 01:24.662
That's not going to make
a damn bit of difference

01:24.703 --> 01:25.752
to our partners.

01:25.791 --> 01:28.066
If we can't prove
that this is reversible,

01:28.099 --> 01:30.101
they're gonna pull the plug.

01:30.134 --> 01:32.301
We'll lose everything.

01:32.543 --> 01:34.072
Do you understand?

01:39.143 --> 01:40.878
This is a radical problem.

01:42.879 --> 01:45.082
Maybe it requires a radical solution.

